The graph in Figure 1.12 is a plot of the collector current \( I_C \) in milliamperes (mA) against the collector-emitter voltage \( V_{CE} \) in volts for an npn bipolar transistor. The graph illustrates the typical \( I_C-V_{CE} \) characteristics, showing distinct regions of operation: saturation, forward active, and inverse active.

